The paper deals with image annotation and tag refinement using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of semantic dependency and user-error sparsity, which are related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
